  "response": "Yes, a US president can resign from office due to stress, frustration, or any other reason. The Constitution outlines the procedure for presidential resignation in Article II, Section 1, Clause 6, which states that the powers and duties of the office devolve to the Vice President in the event of the President's \"Resignation, or Inability to discharge the Powers and Duties of the said Office.\"\n\nWhile it is a rare occurrence, there is historical precedent. Richard Nixon resigned in 1974 in the face of impeachment proceedings.\n\nThe process is simple: the President would typically submit a letter of resignation to the Vice President (who would then become President) and the Speaker of the House.\n",
